<div class="data-container operations-container about-us-page">
    <h1 style="font-size:38px">About IcSMP</h1>

    <h3>Application build by Iordache Catalin</h3>

    <div class="text-aboutus-page">
        <ol class="olcards">
            <li style="--cardColor:#fc374e">
                <div class="content">
                    <div class="icon">😁</div>
                    <div class="title">Short info</div>
                    <div class="text">
                        A stock management software built using the Model-View-Controller (MVC) design pattern is a software system that is designed to handle the inventory management needs of a business or organization. The system comprises three main components, each responsible for specific functions.
                    </div>
                </div>
                &nbsp;
            </li>

            <li style="--cardColor:#0591af">
                <div class="content">
                    <div class="icon">😀</div>
                    <div class="title">Short info</div>
                    <div class="text">
                        The Model component of the stock management software handles the business logic and data storage. It includes the database schema, business objects, and application logic. The database schema defines the structure of the database used to store the inventory data, while the business objects represent the inventory items, suppliers, and customers.
                    </div>
                </div>
                &nbsp;
            </li>

            <li style="--cardColor:#ee82ee">
                <div class="content">
                    <div class="icon">😉</div>
                    <div class="title">Short info</div>
                    <div class="text">
                        The application logic is responsible for processing the user input and updating the inventory data in the database.
                    </div>
                </div>
                &nbsp;
            </li>

            <li style="--cardColor:#0047AB">
                <div class="content">
                    <div class="icon">😀</div>
                    <div class="title">Short info</div>
                    <div class="text">
                        The View component provides the user interface for the stock management software. It is responsible for displaying the inventory data to the user and accepting user input. The View component is implemented using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
                    </div>
                </div>
                &nbsp;
            </li>

            <li style="--cardColor:#fbcc00">
                <div class="content">
                    <div class="icon">😁</div>
                    <div class="title">Short info</div>
                    <div class="text">
                        The Controller component acts as the mediator between the Model and the View components. It handles user requests and invokes the appropriate Model methods to update the inventory data in the database. It also updates the View component to display the updated inventory data to the user.
                    </div>
                </div>
                &nbsp;
            </li>

            <li style="--cardColor:#fc374e">
                <div class="content">
                    <div class="icon">😁</div>
                    <div class="title">Short info</div>
                    <div class="text">
                        The stock management software built using MVC design pattern can provide several benefits to businesses. It allows for a separation of concerns between the different components, making the software more modular and easier to maintain. It also facilitates the testing of individual components and promotes code reusability.
                    </div>
                </div>
                &nbsp;
            </li>

            <li style="--cardColor:#f15f0e">
                <div class="content">
                    <div class="icon">😜</div>
                    <div class="title">Short info</div>
                    <div class="text">
                        Additionally, it provides a consistent user interface and promotes code consistency. Overall, the stock management software built using MVC design pattern can help businesses efficiently manage their inventory and improve their bottom line.
                    </div>
                </div>
                &nbsp;
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>

